# dev-import.sql ŌĆö mandatory dev seed (all features)

[`dev-import.sql`](../../src/main/resources/dev-import.sql) is the **single dev database seed**. It runs on **every** `%dev` startup via [`DatabaseDevSetup`](../../src/main/java/dev/vepo/contraponto/shared/infra/DatabaseDevSetup.java), after Flyway applies migrations.

## Mandatory rule

**Every change that touches persistence, domain entities, or user-facing flows must update `dev-import.sql` in the same PR/session** ŌĆö together with Flyway (`db/migration/`), JPA entities, tests, and docs.

| Trigger | Required `dev-import.sql` action |
|---------|----------------------------------|
| New/changed table or column (Flyway) | INSERT/UPDATE seed rows; satisfy NOT NULL and FKs |
| New entity or repository | Sample rows for local exploration |
| Feature shipped or extended (`done` / `in-progress`) | Happy-path data so `./mvnw quarkus:dev` exercises the feature without manual setup |
| New role or permission | Dev user with that role |
| New UI route with auth gate | Persona that can reach the route |
| Removed feature | Remove obsolete seed; no dead references |

**Forbidden:** marking a feature `done` while `dev-import.sql` lacks happy-path data; schema PR without seed update; relying only on `Given` for manual dev exploration.

Treat **Flyway + `dev-import.sql` + entities** as one deliverable ([development-process.mdc](development-process.mdc)).

## Feature coverage registry

Keep aligned with [feature/](../../feature/) and [docs/feature-catalog.md](../../docs/feature-catalog.md) ┬¦ Dev personas. When a shipped feature reaches `done`, its row must be **Covered**.

| Feature area | Status | Required seed (minimum) |
|--------------|--------|-------------------------|
| Platform admin | Covered | `admin` user + roles; welcome post |
| Multi-blog authors | Covered | `alice`, `bob`, `vepo` (+ secondary `notas` blog) |
| Editor / review | Covered | `editor` user; featured posts for `/review` |
| Reading list | Covered | `dave` follower; reading-list items on seed posts |
| Highlights / responses | Covered | Sample highlights and proposals in dev-import |
| Git sync | Covered | `vepo` blog with Git remote config |
| Notifications / audience | Covered | `tb_notifications`, `tb_blog_audience` samples |
| Custom pages | Covered | Migration footer pages + dev examples |
| Comments moderation | Covered | Sample comments on seed posts |
| Series / tags / RSS / search | Covered | Tagged posts, series membership, pagination volume |
| ActivityPub / Fediverse | Covered | `alice` actor + keys; sample accepted remote follow |

**Agent duty:** on completing a feature changelog entry, update this registry and the SQL file. Open a gap row as **Planned** until seed exists.

## Per-feature checklist (phase 3 / phase 5)

Every feature changelog entry with schema or user-visible behaviour must include:

| ID | Criterion |
|----|-----------|
| **FC*dev*** | `dev-import.sql` covers this feature's happy path |
| **T*dev*** | Update `dev-import.sql` + [feature-catalog.md](../../docs/feature-catalog.md) ┬¦ Dev personas |

